-# Locals: organization, teammate, employee_name, manager_name
- organization = local_assigns.fetch(:organization)
- teammate = local_assigns.fetch(:teammate)
- employee_name = local_assigns.fetch(:employee_name)
- manager_name = local_assigns.fetch(:manager_name)
- teammate_name = teammate.person.casual_name

.alert.alert-light.border.mb-0
  %h3.fw-semibold.mb-2 Goal of this page
  %p.mb-3
    Choose how to move #{teammate_name} toward clarity on where they stand—one item at a time, in bulk, together at finalization, or by reviewing history—and see what is up next for #{employee_name} and #{manager_name}.

  %h3.fw-semibold.mb-2 Context
  = render 'shared/maap/definition'
  = render 'shared/check_ins/three_step_clarity_flow', organization: organization, teammate: teammate, employee_name: employee_name

  %h3.fw-semibold.mb-2 Specifics of this page
  %h5.fw-semibold.mb-2 Clarity health at a glance
  %p.mb-2
    The percentage beside the intro line counts how many required 1-by-1 areas are in a
    %strong crystal-clear
    window (recent check-in activity or finalization). Hover the number for a breakdown by position, assignments, and aspirations.

  %h5.fw-semibold.mb-2 Five ways to check in
  %ul.mb-3
    %li
      %strong Clarity check-in, one at a time
      — primary card; opens the top prioritized aspiration, assignment, or position. Use
      %strong See full queue &amp; why
      on that card for the dual-perspective explainer (
      = link_to 'Up Next', up_next_organization_company_teammate_check_ins_path(organization, teammate)
      ).
    %li
      %strong Bulk clarity check-in
      — rate many areas in one pass (Reflect Apart for everything at once).
    %li
      %strong View latest clarity check-ins
      — spreadsheet-style snapshot of the most recent finalized and open rows.
    %li
      %strong Review together
      — Step Two finalization when both sides have marked ready on the same open check-in (card highlights when any are waiting).
    %li
      %strong Audit / acknowledgements
      — Step Three: MAAP snapshots #{teammate_name} may still need to acknowledge.

  %h5.fw-semibold.mb-2 See what is up next
  %p.mb-0
    The panel at the bottom opens
    = link_to 'Clarity Check-ins... Up Next', up_next_organization_company_teammate_check_ins_path(organization, teammate)
    with side-by-side queues, status pills (hover for why each item ranks where it does), and links when something is ready for #{employee_name} and #{manager_name} to review together.
